================================================================================
MJ2438 – Modeling of Energy Systems
Techno-Economic Assessment: PV + Li-ion Battery + Inverter Subsystem
Location : Seville, Spain  (37.39°N, 5.99°W)
Plant     : 10 MW industrial process-heat plant, 08:00–18:00 local time
Coverage  : PV + Battery covers 40 % of total demand

REVISION — Enhanced Physical Modeling (pvlib-based)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PV Array  (pvlib ModelChain approach, all improvements below):
  1. POA irradiance      – Hay-Davies transposition from TMY DNI + DHI + GHI.
                           Replaces the bare-GHI assumption of the baseline.
  2. Row-to-row shading  – pvlib.shading.shaded_fraction1d applied to the beam
                           component (infinite-sheds 1-D model, Anderson &
                           Jensen 2024). Shading is zero at high elevations and
                           increases as the sun approaches the horizon.
  3. Spectral correction – SAPM spectral mismatch factor (Sandia, monosi
                           coefficients) as a function of absolute air mass
                           computed from the TMY surface-pressure column.
  4. Bifacial gain       – Rear irradiance estimated from albedo × GHI ×
                           (1 – GCR) (simplified Marion et al. infinite-sheds
                           model), attenuated by the panel bifaciality factor.
  5. Cell temperature    – Faiman (1992) / IEC 61853 model using TMY wind speed
                           (WS10m column).  Replaces the NOCT-only formula.
  6. DC power            – pvlib PVWatts v5 model applied to spectral-corrected
                           effective irradiance with the Jinko γ coefficient.
  7. Degradation         – Continuous linear profile within Year 1 (0 → –1 %);
                           cumulative year-on-year from Year 2 onward.
  8. DC string voltage   – Vmp temperature-corrected per string (n_series × Vmp);
                           fed to the inverter MPPT model.

Inverter (Sungrow SG1100UD-20):
  • Three-segment base efficiency curve (loading ratio).
  • DC voltage penalty outside the optimal MPPT window (200–1 500 V range,
    optimal 850–1 350 V).
  • Ambient temperature derating above 40 °C (–0.3 %/°C from rated power).

Weather data:
  All variables (GHI, DNI, DHI, T2m, WS10m, SP) are read from the PVGIS TMY
  CSV file.  A synthetic fallback is provided for development only.

Component Datasheets
────────────────────
PV Panel  : Jinko Solar Tiger Neo 72HL4-BDV 590 Wp (ENF #55991)
            N-type TOPCon bifacial, η = 22.65 %, γ = –0.29 %/°C
Inverter  : Sungrow 1+X Modular (SG1100UD-20), 1.1 MW/module, η > 99 %
Battery   : Tesla Megapack 2 XL – 4-hour config
            979 kW / 3 916 kWh per unit, RTE = 93.7 %

Usage
─────
  python pv_battery_subsystem.py
  python pv_battery_subsystem.py --pvgis path/to/Sevilla_TMY.csv

Download the Seville TMY CSV from:
  https://re.jrc.ec.europa.eu/pvg_tools/en/#TMY
